import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='normal', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['normal'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['normal'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['normal'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['normal'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['day'] = pd.to_datetime(data['day'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['day'])]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='day', y='actual', data=data, label='Actual', ax=ax)
    sns.lineplot(x='day', y='forecast', data=data, label='Forecast', ax=ax)
    plt.title("How does the 'actual' value compare to the 'forecast' value?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Day')
    plt.ylabel('Value')
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['day'] = pd.to_datetime(data['day'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['day'])]
    data['day'] = data['day'].dt.strftime('%Y-%m-%d')
    chart = sns.barplot(x='day', y='record', data=data, ci=None)
    chart.axhline(y=data['record'].median(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Median')
    chart.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['normal'] = pd.to_numeric(data['normal'], errors='coerce')
    data['actual'] = pd.to_numeric(data['actual'], errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna(subset=['normal', 'actual'])
    sns.scatterplot(x='normal', y='actual', data=data)
    plt.title("What is the relationship between 'normal' and 'actual' values?", wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
